  "observations": [
    "Asymmetric dual-surface product: authenticated host dashboard vs stateless guest booking page under public slug URL",
    "EventType as first-class template entity ‚ÄĒ card-grid dashboard with each card representing reusable scheduling configuration (duration + policy + integrations)",
    "Booker flow is a linear 3-step wizard: month calendar ‚Üí slot column ‚Üí form, not a form with all fields at once",
    "Calendar grid shows derived TimeSlot availability by overlaying CalendarIntegration busy-times on AvailabilityRule recurrence ‚ÄĒ slots are computed, not stored",
    "Slot selection acts as primary CTA, bypassing typical list-detail navigation",
    "Reschedule and cancel are stateless ‚ÄĒ accessed via signed ICS token in confirmation email, no account required",
    "Weekly-recurring AvailabilityRule + DateOverride pattern (base schedule + sparse exceptions) rather than storing every available date",
    "Round-robin / collective event-types implied m2m between EventType and TeamMember (host.scope vs team.scope)",
    "Workflow automation uses temporal scheduler: pre-meeting, reminders, follow-up as time-offset triggers relative to Booking.startTime",
    "Payment gate sits between slot selection and Booking confirmation ‚ÄĒ capture_payment is irreversible (__irr high) with no-show deposit auto-capture via schedule rule",
    "Analytics dashboard is aggregation-shaped (by event-type, by time, by source) with CSV export as terminal action",
    "Guest booker has no persistent identity ‚ÄĒ bookerEmail is the de-facto identifier, not a User entity",
    "Calendar integration is single-host-scoped (ownerField: hostId), sync direction declared via writeEvents boolean"
  ]
}